'''Kate Barnow''' is an American [[television writer]], best known for her work on the [[HBO]] vampire series ''[[True Blood]]''. She often works on projects with her writing partner [[Elisabeth R. Finch]].
== Early career == Barnow began her television career working as an assistant to the [[executive producer]]s on the [[situation comedy|sitcom]] ''[[Will & Grace]]''. She then worked as a script co-ordinator on the short-lived ''[[Studio 60 on the Sunset Strip]]''. She, along with Finch, were then hired as writer's assistants on ''True Blood'' for the second season. Her writing debut came with the tenth episode of that season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2422433/|title=Kate Barnow|work=IMDb|accessdate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>
== ''True Blood'' episodes == *2.10 ''New World in My View'' *3.4 ''9 Crimes'' *3.10 ''I Smell a Rat'' *6.7 ''In the Evening'' *6.10 ''Radioactive'' *7.2 ''I Found You'' *7.8 ''Almost Home''
