'''Meccanoid''' is a highly intelligent programmable robot.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Meccanoid|url=http://www.meccano.com/meccanoid-about|publisher=Meccano|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> It was created by [[Meccano]], the model construction system created in Liverpool, United Kingdom, by [[Frank Hornby]] and now based in Calais, France.

The Meccanoid was described by ''[[Popular Science]]'' as "The smartest DIY bot to ever spill out of a box"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nuñez|first1=Michael|title=Build up your imagination with the Meccanoid kit|url=http://www.popsci.com/build-your-imagination-meccanoid-kit|website=Popular Science|accessdate=16 November 2015|date=18 August 2015}}</ref> and the G15 robot featured in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine's 2015 article: "These Are the Gadgets Everybody Wants This Holiday".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pullen|first1=John Patrick|title=These Are the Gadgets Everybody Wants This Holiday|url=http://time.com/4114204/holiday-gadgets-gifts-tech-shopping/|website=TIME|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> 

