{{for|the Irish draughts player|Patricia Breen (draughts player)}} {{BLP sources|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox person |name = Patricia Breen |image = |caption = |birth_date = |birth_name = |birth_place = [[United States]] |occupation = [[Television writer]], [[Television producer|producer]] |yearsactive = 2002&ndash;present }}
'''Patricia Breen''' is an American [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]], who has worked on a range of shows including ''[[Frasier]]'' and the acclaimed [[HBO]] [[polygamy]] drama ''[[Big Love]]''.
== Career == Breen began her writing career on the [[Frasier (season 10)|tenth season]] of ''Frasier''. She worked as a story editor on the [[Frasier (season 11)|eleventh and final]] season while also contributing two scripts. In 2006 she wrote a pilot script for [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] called ''[[Pink Collar]]'' starring [[Alicia Silverstone]]. The pilot was not successful in securing a series order. In 2009 she joined the writing staff of ''Big Love'' for its third season. She was a co-producer in season four and a producer in its fifth and final season. She contributed one script each season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.film.com/celebrities/patricia-breen/14839356|title=Patricia Breen from Big Love|work=Film.com|accessdate=January 22, 2011}}</ref>
